  "prompt": "What type of grapes are used to make wine?",
  "response": "Wine is primarily made from different species of grapes, most notably Vitis vinifera, which is the species that includes the majority of wine grape varieties. Within this species, there are thousands of grape varieties used to produce wine. Some of the most popular wine grape varieties include:\n\n1. **Cabernet Sauvignon**: Known for its thick skin and high tannins, commonly used in red wines.\n\n2. **Merlot**: Softer than Cabernet Sauvignon, often used in blends and as a single variety wine.\n\n3. **Pinot Noir**: A red grape associated with lighter-bodied wines, known for its complexity and ability to reflect terroir.\n\n4. **Syrah/Shiraz**: Known for producing full-bodied red wines with spicy notes.\n\n5. **Chardonnay**: One of the most popular white wine grapes, known for its versatility and ability to be oaked or unoaked.\n\n6. **Sauvignon Blanc**: A green-skinned grape known for its crisp, aromatic white wines.\n\n7. **Riesling**: Known for producing aromatic wines that can range from dry to sweet.\n\n8. **Zinfandel**: Predominantly grown in California, it produces robust red wines and is also used for making White Zinfandel, a popular ros\u00e9.\n\nThese are just a few examples, and there are many other grape varieties used around the world, each contributing unique flavors and characteristics to wines. Each region may have its own traditional grape varieties that reflect the local climate, soil, and winemaking traditions.",
